<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp30217376">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp245602592">
<p id="fs-idm25604816">Write the Lewis structures for the following, and include resonance structures where appropriate. Indicate which has the strongest carbon-oxygen bond.</p>
<p id="fs-idp9268576">(a) CO<sub>2</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idm17614608">(b) CO</p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-idp32842640">
<p id="fs-idp32184800">(a)<span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
</p><span data-type="media" id="fs-idm35689072" data-alt="This structure shows a carbon atom double bonded to two oxygen atoms, each of which has two lone pairs of electrons.">
<img src="/resources/27df3f8404cacaf02741773e0b28767d57fa4e95/CNX_Chem_07_04_Ques13ansb_img.jpg" data-media-type="image/jpeg" alt="This structure shows a carbon atom double bonded to two oxygen atoms, each of which has two lone pairs of electrons."/>
</span><p><span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
(b)<span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
</p><span data-type="media" id="fs-idp52448512" data-alt="The right structure of this pair shows a carbon atom with one lone pair of electrons triple bonded to an oxygen with one lone pair of electrons.">
<img src="/resources/c1886daeb3af0f88c21c92eb795b54ac155a19f7/CNX_Chem_07_04_Ques13ansc_img.jpg" data-media-type="image/jpeg" alt="The right structure of this pair shows a carbon atom with one lone pair of electrons triple bonded to an oxygen with one lone pair of electrons."/>
</span><p><span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
CO has the strongest carbon-oxygen bond because there is a triple bond joining C and O. CO<sub>2</sub> has double bonds.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp29752720">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp190371664">
<p id="fs-idm15185536">Toothpastes containing sodium hydrogen carbonate (sodium bicarbonate) and hydrogen peroxide are widely used. Write Lewis structures for the hydrogen carbonate ion and hydrogen peroxide molecule, with resonance forms where appropriate.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp23408944">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm62310560">
<p id="fs-idp134601472">Determine the formal charge of each element in the following:</p>
<p id="fs-idp36610048">(a) HCl</p>
<p id="fs-idp223116352">(b) CF<sub>4</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idm16885392">(c) PCl<sub>3</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idm32027408">(d) PF<sub>5</sub></p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-idp93168608">
<p id="fs-idm21325744">(a) H: 0, Cl: 0; (b) C: 0, F: 0; (c) P: 0, Cl 0; (d) P: 0, F: 0</p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idm33617232">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp99546640">
