<p id="fs-idp87268656">(a) H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup></p>
<p id="fs-idp28450944">(b) <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mtext>SO</mtext><mn>4</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>2&#8722;</mtext></msup></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mtext>SO</mtext><mn>4</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>2&#8722;</mtext></msup></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
<p id="fs-idp109041968">(c) NH<sub>3</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idp47951984">(d) <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mtext>O</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>2&#8722;</mtext></msup></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mtext>O</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>2&#8722;</mtext></msup></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
<p id="fs-idp91448368">(e) H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub></p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp25221456">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp8015248">
<p id="fs-idp137795936">Calculate the formal charge of chlorine in the molecules Cl<sub>2</sub>, BeCl<sub>2</sub>, and ClF<sub>5</sub>.</p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-idp31585296">
<p id="fs-idm369848352">Cl in Cl<sub>2</sub>: 0; Cl in BeCl<sub>2</sub>: 0; Cl in ClF<sub>5</sub>: 0</p>
</div>
</div>
